    <h3> Steffi </h3>
    <p> After checking out at the campsite this morning, we left the car in the parking lot in front of the entrance and took the bus to the city center by bus, as we wanted to visit the Queen Victoria Markt again and one or the other in the city. </p>
    <p> Here it was quick to get gifts for the loved ones at home. When we bought everything, we headed the City Tourist Shuttlebus. This is free and drives you across the city. At the royal botanical garden, the journey was over for us and we first headed for the war monument before we then moved into the green oasis. After a short time we sat on a park bench and enjoyed nothing to do for a few minutes. When we continued, we passed a parking restaurant/ caf&eacute; and we treated ourselves to ice chocolate! This was not as tasty as the two days earlier, but as a drink in between, it was ok. </p>
    <p> Shortly afterwards we came from the botanical garden at the Yarra-River and slowly made our way towards the city center. Always nicely along the river, accompanied by a rowing competition that was just taking place. </p>
