    <p> A free parking for Hugo was quickly found and we started. Passing the harbor basin, where it was boiling in the water, but you couldn't see who organized it. The path continued past the pier, whereupon a restaurant or the like was built together with parking spaces until the next ice cream truck. This attracted our attention. We have wanted ice all the time, but we have never struck because the prices are simply too exchanged. Well, in the end we also left almost $ 12.00 for 2 ice cream that didn't even taste good! Slowly the sun went down and we continued to walk to the Ferris wheel, which we made out at some distance. However, there was not too much to be seen here and so we went back to Hugo, now at moonlight. Of course not without taking one or the other photo on the way! </p>
    <p> When we got back to Hugo, we finished everything so far so that after the cat washing at the fast food chain we could jump into the car. But there it was first said "hunting mosquito". Yes, these beasts really follow us and the lake in front of the car didn't make it better. </p>
